'''Seol Young-woo''' ({{korean|설영우}}; born 5 December 1998) is a South Korean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[full-back (association football)|full-back]] for [[Serbian SuperLiga]] club [[Red Star Belgrade]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kfa.or.kr/archive/player_record.php?search_val=%EC%84%A4%EC%98%81%EC%9A%B0 |title=Seol Young-woo at Korea Football Association |language=ko |publisher=KFA |access-date=2023-10-16}}</ref>

== Club career ==

=== Ulsan HD ===
Born in [[Ulsan]], Seol played as a youth player for hometown team Ulsan Hyundai (renamed [[Ulsan HD FC|Ulsan HD]] in 2024) since childhood. After attending university for a while, he played for the senior team of Ulsan Hyundai since 2020. He contributed to Ulsan's two [[K League 1]] titles in 2022 and 2023. On 1 October 2024, he was nominated for the [[Asian Footballer of the Year#AFC award|AFC Player of the Year]] for 2023 by helping his club and national team reach the semi-finals of the [[2023–24 AFC Champions League]] and the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]], respectively, in addition to the league title.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/about_afc/afc_annual_awards/news/afc_annual_awards_seoul_2023_nominees_revealed.html |title=AFC Annual Awards Seoul 2023 nominees revealed |publisher=AFC |date=2024-10-01 |access-date=2024-10-22}}</ref>

=== Red Star Belgrade ===
On 29 June 2024, Seol moved to [[Serbian SuperLiga]] club [[Red Star Belgrade]] for an undisclosed fee on a three-year contract with an option for a one-year extension.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.crvenazvezdafk.com/vesti/jung-vu-seol-potpisao-za-crvenu-zvezdu |title=Јунг Ву Сеол потписао за Црвену звезду |language=sr |publisher=Red Star Belgrade |date=2024-06-29 |access-date=2024-11-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.kleagueunited.com/2024/06/official-seol-young-woo-moves-to.html |title=Official: Seol Young-woo moves to Serbian side FK Crvena zvezda |publisher=K League United |date=2024-06-24 |access-date=2024-11-12}}</ref> He provided three assists in eight [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|league phase]] matches during his first [[UEFA Champions League]] season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/clubs/players/250189363--youngwoo-seol/statistics/ |title=Youngwoo Seol |publisher=UEFA |access-date=2025-02-10}}</ref> For two years, he helped the club win two [[Double (association football)|Double]]s,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.crvenazvezdafk.com/sr-latn/vesti/sixth-double-crown-in-a-row |title=Sixth double crown in a row |publisher=Red Star Belgrade |date=2026-05-14 |access-date=2026-05-20}}</ref> and was selected for the [[Serbian SuperLiga Team of the Season|league's Team of the Season]] twice.<ref name="25tots"/><ref name="26tots"/>

== International career ==
Seol was called up for the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]] for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]]. He underachieved in the group stage, and conceded a penalty against [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.footballist.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=178659 |script-title=ko:[알와크라 라이브] 설영우 "왼쪽? 오른쪽? 감독님이 내보내주기만 하면 시키는 대로 뛴다" |language=ko |publisher=Footballist |date=2024-01-26 |access-date=2024-02-11}}</ref> He provided an accurate cross, assisting [[Cho Gue-sung]]'s equalising header in second-half stoppage time of the round of 16 match against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]].  He showed tremendous workrate by moving 15.54&nbsp;km in the quarter-final match against [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] and was selected for the team of the matchday after the match,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/AFCAsianCup/photos/these-players-brought-exceptional-performances-to-the-pitch-%EF%B8%8Fvisit-saudi-asiancu/945805160248902/ |title=These players brought exceptional performances to the pitch! |website=Facebook.com |publisher=AFC Asian Cup |date=2024-02-04 |access-date=2024-02-11}}</ref> although he took a rest for only two days after the round of 16.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://medium.com/@123dreamingofyou/asian-cup-seol-young-woo-15-5km-9f11a45ae7f3 |title=[Asian Cup] 'Seol Young-woo 15.5km — Son Heung-min 14.5km' The distance he played after two days off, won the match against Australia with 'spirit'. |publisher=Medium |access-date=2024-02-11}}</ref> South Korea was eliminated in the semi-finals by [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]], but found solace in a new full-back.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/football/2024/02/08/PC7PD4Q6WZHD5LUTNQPYQYCOZA/ |script-title=ko:귀한 측면 수비 찾았다… 설영우, 亞컵 유일 수확 |language=ko |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |date=2024-02-08 |access-date=2024-02-11}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Seol had played as a [[Forward (association football)#Winger|winger]] until his university days, but changed his role to a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] at the start of his professional career.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.footballist.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=161337 |script-title=ko:[전훈 인터뷰] '난 울산 칸셀루' 설영우 "언젠가 대표팀에서 규성이 형처럼" |publisher=Footballist |language=ko |date=2023-01-17 |access-date=2023-10-16}}</ref> He is a right-footed full-back, but could be deployed on both left and right flank.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.news.nate.com/view/20230320n17406 |script-title=ko:울산 설영우, 홍心 잡고 전천후 풀백으로 진화 |publisher=Sportalkorea |website=[[Nate (web portal)|Nate]] |language=ko |date=2023-03-20 |access-date=2023-10-16}}</ref>

